China has allocated 200 million yuan for disaster relief following a devastating earthquake in Sichuan that claimed over 8,700 lives.
The quake, with a magnitude of 7.8, struck densely populated areas, including the capital Chengdu.
Russia's President Dmitry Medvedev offered condolences and assistance to China.
Despite high earthquake prediction levels, no warning signs were detected before the disaster.
Rainfall in the coming days may hamper relief efforts and increase landslide risks.
Various countries, including Germany and Norway, have pledged aid to support China in this time of crisis.
The international community stands in solidarity with the affected regions.
